HEADWORD: Kauri copal
<hw>Kauri
copal</hw> }</mhw>. <def>A resinous product of the
<prodby>kauri</prodby>, found in the form of yellow or brown lumps in
the ground where the trees have grown. It is used for making varnish,
and as a substitute for amber.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

